# Source Folder

Here you will find the source code for the main program for the Robotics AI project, as well as for the rest of the modules.

The code is split up based on the robotics process: AI Decision Layer, Localization, TF Monitoring, PX4 Control, and ROS 2 Basic Nodes. All folders have a corresponding text explaining the functions of that part of the code.

## Folder Structure

### AI Decision Layer

This folder contains the source code for the AI decision logic in the project. In this project, the simulated gas or leak-risk values are used to decide the state of the drone mission.

The decision logic utilizes the risk values and determines a particular mission state from the states listed below.

- `SEARCH`
- `INVESTIGATE`
- `CONFIRM_HOVER`

These states are used to determine the course of action for the drone in the control layer.

### Localization

This folder contains code used for both odometry and localization. This includes how the drone simulation tracks the drone’s movement within the simulation environment and how different types of data can be used to find and track the drone for localization.

This project takes the pose information from Gazebo and converts it into ROS 2 odometry messages and transform messages so that other parts of the program can know where the drone is located.

### TF Monitoring

This folder contains files for monitoring and validation of transform frames.

TF frames are used throughout ROS 2 to describe the relationship between different coordinate frames.

- `map`
- `odom`
- `base_link`
- `link`

From the above frames, you can confirm the proper alignment between localization, SLAM information, and the drone body.

### PX4 Control

This folder contains the source code for PX4 offboard control.

The PX4 control layer receives mission decisions and converts them into PX4-compatible setpoints and commands. The control layer publishes setpoints and commands to PX4 topics so that the drone can move according to the current mission state.

### ROS2 Basic Nodes

# ROS 2 Publisher and Subscriber Examples

This package contains simple ROS 2 publisher and subscriber examples to test and get familiar with ROS 2 communication capabilities.

This section shows how to use topics, publishers, and subscribers to connect different parts of the system.

## Purpose of This Folder

This is the `src/` folder for the project, where the implementation code lives. This includes ROS 2 communication, localization, AI decision code, and PX4 control integration, overall forming the Robotics AI pipeline.

This folder contains the development of the drone system as individual parts and then shows the simulation of the drone reacting to simulated gas leak-risk values by linking all of the parts together.
